---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import SEO from '../../components/SEO.astro';

const usageSnippet = `---
import { SEO } from 'comet-astro';

---

<SEO
  title="About Us"
  description="Learn more about our company, mission, and values."
  keywords={["company", "about", "mission", "values"]}
  type="website"
  image="/og-about.jpg"
  imageAlt="Our team working together"
/>`;

const breadcrumbsSnippet = `---
import { SEO } from 'comet-astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: "Home", url: "/" },
  { name: "Products", url: "/products" },
  { name: "Smartphones", url: "/products/smartphones" }
];
---

<SEO
  title="Smartphones"
  description="Discover our latest smartphone collection."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  showBreadcrumbs={true}
  type="website"
/>`;

const articleSnippet = `---
import { SEO } from 'comet-astro';

---

<SEO
  title="How to Build Better Websites"
  description="A comprehensive guide to modern web development."
  type="article"
  article={{
    publishedTime: "2024-01-15T10:00:00Z",
    modifiedTime: "2024-01-20T14:30:00Z",
    author: ["John Doe", "Jane Smith"],
    section: "Web Development",
    tags: ["html", "css", "javascript", "accessibility"]
  }}
  image="/article-hero.jpg"
  imageAlt="Code editor showing HTML markup"
/>`;
---

<DocsLayout
  title="SEO"
  description="Comprehensive SEO component with WCAG AAA compliance, structured data, and optional visual breadcrumbs."
>
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <p class="text-base text-slate-100">
      The SEO component manages all aspects of search engine optimization
      including meta tags, Open Graph data, Twitter Cards, and structured data
      (JSON-LD). It ensures WCAG AAA compliance with optional visual breadcrumbs
      and proper accessibility attributes.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Built for both website and article content types, it handles complex
      scenarios like article metadata, social media integration, and
      comprehensive structured data while maintaining clean, semantic HTML
      output.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Props</h2>
    <dl class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          title
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Page title that will be combined with the site name. Used for <code
            >&lt;title&gt;</code
          >, Open Graph, and Twitter Card meta tags.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          description?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Meta description for search engines and social media previews.
          Recommended length: 150-160 characters.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          keywords?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Array of keywords or comma-separated string. Used for meta keywords
          and structured data.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          type?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Content type for Open Graph and structured data. Options: <code
            >"website"</code
          >,
          <code>"article"</code>, <code>"profile"</code>, <code>"book"</code>.
          Defaults to <code>"website"</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          image?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Featured image URL for social media previews. Automatically converted
          to absolute URL if relative.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          imageAlt?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Alt text for the featured image. Required for accessibility when image
          is provided.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          breadcrumbs?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Array of breadcrumb objects with <code>name</code> and <code>url</code
          >
          properties. Generates structured data and optional visual navigation.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          showBreadcrumbs?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Whether to render visual breadcrumb navigation with WCAG AAA compliant
          styling. Defaults to <code>false</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          article?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Article-specific metadata object with <code>publishedTime</code>,
          <code>modifiedTime</code>, <code>author</code>, <code>section</code>,
          and <code>tags</code> properties.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          openGraph?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Open Graph specific overrides for title, description, image, type,
          locale, and site name.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          twitterCard?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Twitter Card specific settings including card type, site handle,
          creator, and custom content.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm sm:col-span-2"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          structuredData?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Additional structured data to merge with the automatically generated
          schema. Useful for custom schema types and properties.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Basic Usage</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Import the component and provide essential SEO information. The component
      automatically handles URL resolution, structured data generation, and
      accessibility attributes.
    </p>
    <pre
      class="overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-slate-700/70 bg-slate-950/80 p-4 text-sm text-slate-50 shadow-inner">
      <code class="language-astro">{usageSnippet}</code>
    </pre>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Visual Breadcrumbs</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Enable visual breadcrumb navigation with WCAG AAA compliant styling.
      Breadcrumbs provide both structured data for search engines and accessible
      navigation for users.
    </p>
    <pre
      class="overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-slate-700/70 bg-slate-950/80 p-4 text-sm text-slate-50 shadow-inner">
      <code class="language-astro">{breadcrumbsSnippet}</code>
    </pre>

    <!-- Demo breadcrumbs -->
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700/70 bg-slate-900/40 p-6">
      <SEO
        title="Demo Page"
        breadcrumbs={[
          { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
          { name: 'Components', url: '/components' },
          { name: 'SEO', url: '/components/seo' },
        ]}
        showBreadcrumbs={true}
        class="!mb-0"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Article Content</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      For article pages, provide additional metadata to enhance search engine
      understanding and social media previews. The component automatically
      generates Article schema and appropriate Open Graph tags.
    </p>
    <pre
      class="overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-slate-700/70 bg-slate-950/80 p-4 text-sm text-slate-50 shadow-inner">
      <code class="language-astro">{articleSnippet}</code>
    </pre>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Accessibility</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Visual breadcrumbs maintain WCAG AAA contrast ratios (9:1) in both light
      and dark themes. Focus indicators use 2px ring width with appropriate
      offset for clear visibility against all backgrounds.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      The component includes proper ARIA labels, semantic navigation markup, and
      structured data that screen readers can parse. All image tags include alt
      text requirements and proper role attributes.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">SEO Features</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-200">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
        <span class="text-green-400 mt-1">✓</span>
        Complete meta tag generation (title, description, keywords, robots)
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
        <span class="text-green-400 mt-1">✓</span>
        Open Graph and Twitter Card support with image optimization
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
        <span class="text-green-400 mt-1">✓</span>
        Structured data (JSON-LD) for websites and articles
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
        <span class="text-green-400 mt-1">✓</span>
        Canonical URL handling with automatic resolution
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
        <span class="text-green-400 mt-1">✓</span>
        Breadcrumb structured data and visual navigation
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
        <span class="text-green-400 mt-1">✓</span>
        Article metadata with author, publish date, and tags
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
        <span class="text-green-400 mt-1">✓</span>
        Language and locale specification
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
        <span class="text-green-400 mt-1">✓</span>
        Custom structured data merging
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
